{"TopicId":100722,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Now this is pod racing mk2","CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T19:50:00Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T19:50:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter trying my best to build a completely stock pod racer i was not 100% happy with the results,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo i ended up resorting to a few mods and here are fruits of my labour.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ENow this is pod racing mk2\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228HmUF3S.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/8HmUF3S.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022BHxtY1Y.jpg\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/BHxtY1Y.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/O-QMPSTo0K0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EDescription: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ultimate in pod racing technology, this craft will put a smile on any kerbals dial, capable of over 140m/s and reliably going over rough terrain this baby is sure to kill some of your afternoon around the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry to the laptop users but the part count is high, i could not keep it low and have it function. (Thats a lite i could have but aesthetics \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022\u003E)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELaunch instructions: \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPress 1 until the craft is sitting on the ground, decouple the command pod and EVA your kerbal, go and attach both winches to the pod racer engine then board the craft, press 2 until the craft is as high as it will go then decouple the mount on the engines first then the mount on the pod, Change controls to the pod racer engines not the pod itself, right click the command unit and press \u0022control from here\u0022 turn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on the engines on and away you go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EAction groups: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1 - Lower craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 - Raise craft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3 - Toggle engines\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ERequired mods: \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbal Attachment System.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.curse.com/ksp-mods/kerbal/223900-kerbal-attachment-system-kas\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.curse.com/ksp-mods/kerbal/223900-kerbal-attachment-system-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003Ekas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbal foundries wheels and repolsors.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgba(242,199,68,0.1);color:#1d1c1d;font-size:15px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E[Moderator removed defunct website link]\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDownload link: \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003Epart count: 354\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www./download/aa8tl2cri2p9m8e/Now\u002Bthis\u002Bis\u002Bpod\u002Bracing\u002Bmk2.craft\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ehttp://www./download/aa8tl2cri2p9m8e/Now\u002Bthis\u002Bis\u002Bpod\u002Bracing\u002Bmk2.craft\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow this is pod racing mk1 forum location:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/111443-Now-this-is-pod-racing\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttp://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/111443-Now-this-is-pod-racing\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-08-28T15:15:46Z\u0022 title=\u002208/28/2022 03:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 28, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by James Kerman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Elink removed\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darren9","CreatedById":58062,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T20:05:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI like the design but I think it needs Quantum Struts for the energy coupling in the middle. They also go a lot better with a Firespitter/B9 airbrake on the pod, it keeps the cables tighter.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T20:06:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Darren9\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Darren9\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI like the design but I think it needs Quantum Struts for the energy coupling in the middle. They also go a lot better with a Firespitter/B9 airbrake on the pod, it keeps the cables tighter.\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI wanted to use quantum struts but i could not get it to work on my KSP \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E built this on 0.90.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOh and for some weird reason any aerodynamic parts on the pod were making the engines cut out when the pod was directly behind them, why i ended up going for a structural part only pod design\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-02-25T20:10:04Z\u0022 title=\u002202/25/2015 08:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 25, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Roflcopterkklol\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darren9","CreatedById":58062,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T20:09:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Roflcopterkklol\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Roflcopterkklol\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI wanted to use quantum struts but i could not get it to work on my KSP \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003EI don\u0027t think I\u0027ve tried them in 0.90, it could be the end of energy couplings \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T20:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Darren9\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Darren9\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EI don\u0027t think I\u0027ve tried them in 0.90, it could be the end of energy couplings \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYeah seems the mod author has not updated it to 0.90, shame.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T20:44:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENow that\u0027s absolute brilliance right there \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T22:14:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022 data-cite=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ENow that\u0027s absolute brilliance right there \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThanks man glad you like it \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starwhip","CreatedById":83990,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T22:19:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBah, it uses antigrav repulsors. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther than that, it\u0027s pretty great! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Roflcopterkklol","CreatedById":119190,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-25T22:21:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starwhip\u0022 data-cite=\u0022S